        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 3:43PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 342 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ingram, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Turbeville...
Ingram...
Milton...
Elmo...
Ringgold...
and Keeling.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
